===Etymology 1===
{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|むな}}
From {{inh|ja|ojp|-|sort=むな}}. First attested in the ''{{w|Kojiki}}'' of 712 {{CE}}.<ref name="KDJ2O_muna">{{R:Nihon Kokugo Daijiten 2 Online|むな 【胸】|lid=2002041617aeDDaJg2v4}}</ref> Possibly the original form of ''mune'' below.

The first edition of the Nihon Kokugo Daijiten says that this is cognate with {{m|ja|棟|tr=muna||main roofline, roof ridge}}, from the underlying idea of ''central or main portion''.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref> However, see Etymology 2.

Possibly also related with {{m|ja|空}}, {{m|ja|虚|tr=muna||emptiness, void}}, from the idea of ''cavity''.

Seldom used in isolation even in Old Japanese. Only found as the first element of compounds in modern Japanese.<ref name="KDJ2O_muna"/><ref name="DJR">{{R:Daijirin}}</ref>

